    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-27T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-27T10:00:00-05:00" n="147"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.24/104: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-27T09:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 27, 1940—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>117. My telegram No. 115, November 25, 3 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>] p.m. The
                    Foreign Minister has just sent me memorandum referring to our <pb facs="0133"
                        n="121" xml:id="pg_121"/> conversation of the 25th and saying that the
                    Guatemalan Government would be pleased to have a United States Army officer sent
                    to Guatemala to make a survey of Guatemalan military needs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
